Article ID   : 3
Title        : Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) — Attack Atlas
Category     : web
Exported by  : sentinel-export-service v1.4.0
Export time  : 2026-03-15T11:00:00Z
Classification: INTERNAL

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SSRF allows an attacker to induce the server-side application
to make HTTP requests to an arbitrary domain of the attacker's
choosing. When the server can reach internal infrastructure,
SSRF becomes a critical finding.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SENTINEL PLATFORM TEST TARGETS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The SENTINEL network scanner tool (POST /api/tools/ping) is
vulnerable to SSRF. The host field is not validated against
an allowlist.

Test payloads:
  {"host": "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/"}
  {"host": "http://0.0.0.0:5000/api/admin/credentials"}
  {"host": "http://localhost:5432/"}

